headline: Salesforce forecasts annual revenue below estimates, shares fall
summary: Salesforce forecast fiscal 2027 revenue below Wall Street expectations on Wednesday, ‌signaling sluggish spending on enterprise business software ‌as it invests heavily in its artificial intelligence platform to ​drive up demand. Shares of the San Francisco-based company fell nearly 4% in extended trading, having lost over 28% this year. It expects annual revenue in the ‌range of $45.80 billion ⁠to $46.20 billion, with the midpoint coming in slightly below an estimate of $46.06 billion, ⁠according to data compiled by LSEG.
